alwaysApply: true
---

# WCAG 2.1 AA Compliance (Minimum)
- Color contrast: 4.5:1 for normal text, 3:1 for large text
- NEVER use color alone to convey information (add icons/text)
- All interactive elements keyboard accessible (Tab order)
- Focus indicators visible on all focusable elements

# Semantic HTML
- Use correct landmark elements: <header>, <nav>, <main>, <footer>
- Headings in proper order: h1 → h2 → h3 (no skipping)
- Buttons for actions, links for navigation (don't mix them up)
- Form inputs always have associated <label>

# ARIA
- Use semantic HTML first, ARIA only when HTML falls short
- aria-label for icon-only buttons
- aria-expanded for collapsible content
- aria-live for dynamic status messages
- role="alert" for error messages

# Screen Readers
- Alt text for all informative images (empty alt for decorative)
- Hidden text for visual-only cues (.sr-only class)
- Status updates announced (form submission, errors)
- Skip navigation link for keyboard users

# Testing
- Run axe DevTools on every page
- Tab through entire flow with keyboard only
- Test with actual screen reader (NVDA/VoiceOver) for critical flows
